, and deeply insightful, Rabbi Thorne’s firsthand account offers a rediscovered perspective on the twentieth century’s greatest tragedy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, Jewish. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aIsaac Bashevis Singer, Leon Thorne, rabbi, shoah, Eastern Galicia, Poland, Out of The Ashes, Janowska Camp, Lemberg, World War II, WWII, Jew, Jewish, refugee, concentration camps.1 aMagilow, Daniel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSinger, Isaac Bashevis.1 aThorne, Emanuel, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311065352640uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197880168440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978801684423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978801684/original  a978-3-11-065352-6  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK